### Tested versions

4.4 Stable mono, 4.4.1 Stable mono

### System information

Godot Engine v4.4.1.stable.mono.official.49a5bc7b6 - https://godotengine.org Vulkan 1.3.277 - Forward+ - Using Device #0: NVIDIA - NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1070

### Issue description

I have a total of 3 Exported Arrays of Nodes in my c# game project. I tried to use these to reference a list of Control Button Nodes but my code always reads this array's length is zero only in exported .exe production builds. 
When I started to inspect this issue in my editor, I can't reproduce it. When I changed a bit of code to print the length of the array in the production console (which get me the length 0 result), It started appearing too in the editor.
Sometimes I have the error popup saying: "Failed to get property <something> from node".

My final solution to this is I cleaned all reference in editor, made the exported property have a initial array which is not null, closed the editor, **deleted the .godot folder in my project directory**, restarted editor and redid the reference to the nodes.
I am aware that this bug report does almost nothing in terms of solving the bug, but I was frustruated when searching solutions on the internet as no google results seems to have a solve to this issue.
**I hope this method could help someone out when encountering this bug.**

### Steps to reproduce

```
public partial class UiPauseMenu : Control {
    [Export] public Array<Button> MenuButtons { get; set; };

    public override void _Ready()
    {
        GD.Print($"The length of the buttons array is {MenuButtons.Count}");
        for (int i = 0; i < MenuButtons.Count; i++)
        {
            int i1 = i;
            Instance.MenuButtons[i].Connect("pressed",Callable.From((() =>
            {
                ClickButton(i1);
            })));
        }
    }
}
```

1. Attach this script to a node, populate the array in the editor.
2. Export the project to Windows executable and launch in console mode.
3. The console should say the length is 0 even if it is populated in the editor.
